feat(site): instant CSS tooltip for abbr + wider abbr coverage

Hover behaviour
- Native browser title tooltips take ~1 second to appear in most
  browsers, and several users found "nothing happens on hover". Added
  a custom CSS tooltip on abbr[title] using an ::after pseudo-element
  with content: attr(title). It appears instantly on :hover and on
  :focus-visible, keyboard users included. Also rendered a small
  tooltip arrow via ::before. Styled with the ink background, 280px
  max width, rounded corners, shadow, clean sans-serif.

Wider abbr coverage
- Stack tiles now wrap: MLP, OMOP (+ OMOP-CDM), FedAvg, FedProx,
  FedSGDClassifier, Joye-Libert, OPACUS, ETL, APPI, GDPR, SHAP.
- Evaluation tile wraps: AUROC, AUPRC, Brier, ICI, DCA.
- Regulatory status wraps: CSE, IRB, DPIA, GDPR, CE, MDR, PMDA,
  SaMD, MR-003/MR-004, APPI.
- Each abbr uses a localised title: English definitions in en,
  Japanese in ja, French in fr. Total: 36 abbr tags in en / 36 in
  ja / 35 in fr (MR-003/MR-004 consolidates to one tag).
- HTML attrs for how.item_model, how.item_baseline, how.item_privacy,
  how.item_harmo, how.item_explain, how.eval, how.endpoint, reg.p2
  switched from data-i18n to data-i18n-html so the new abbr / anchor
  tags render through the sanitiser.
- Sanitiser in i18n.js already permits abbr + title from the last
  commit; no further JS changes needed.

i18n parity preserved at 235 keys.
